<subSubSection id="4BB8D704DACBD022443932E3E7169031" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9742978D502ED59195C0733C75DCB9D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="254C11985C495435FB05376271D07A15" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="F059321512B4AB99482FBCF5423C6415" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Dlussky &amp; Zabelin" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax anodontoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="8454FA5A5D7A4BEDA18DC324BCA34347" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Temnothorax anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only member of the group with entirely absent propodeal spines. Additionally, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="13BE75B4E9BCFD584463F1CDA19B0E70" genus="T." lsidName="T. arkasi" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="arkasi">
<emphasis id="E9CAFA48F4AC37D6CAEF87DDEB97553D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. arkasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2AD359ACE07ED941674125FB52538C30" genus="T." lsidName="T. euboeae" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="euboeae">
<emphasis id="B2DEB00D6EA69EBBC10B8A90C649174A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. euboeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B80428EB8E437FAB6D05FCDC7B9CB075" genus="T." lsidName="T. ikarosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="ikarosi">
<emphasis id="9AC90A1E3BE849B82E3B3D39D4BB6F48" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. ikarosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in strongly reduced sculpture on frons, and from 
<taxonomicName id="1931DD8A8D44417B1AD2FB444D25F04C" genus="T." lsidName="T. parnonensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="parnonensis">
<emphasis id="8CA02CE3A2FB1074455E30E86479519B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. parnonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lack of smooth notch on central frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6E0AAC7FD770710745AFE22DCDB7BCA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="369F09D9AFE97943AABDB729067A9367" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD1A64E50995F8BB5E101BEA63F1648B" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<bibRefCitation id="0D3C0D61525A5BEE30669F6BB958D187" author="Dlussky, GM" editor="Nechaevaya, NT" journalOrPublisher="Ashkhabad: Ylym" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="208 - 246" refId="B8" refString="Dlussky, GM, Zabelin, SI, 1985. Ant fauna (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) of the River Sumbar Basin (south-west Kopetdag). In: Nechaevaya, NT, Ed., The vegetation and animal world of western Kopetdag. Ashkhabad: Ylym: 208 - 246" title="Ant fauna (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) of the River Sumbar Basin (south-west Kopetdag)." volumeTitle="The vegetation and animal world of western Kopetdag." year="1985">Dlussky and Zabelin (1985)</bibRefCitation>
: 227.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AF2739AB9E11CC84F910280F178F93F" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="92EB0E66FF0F1953A8E4244B5764C9DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="843ED4D6874912C9113F2210FA786184" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Kopet Dag, Turkmenistan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1447A9D160F4E55584FC635D252C79F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="comments">
<paragraph id="8235D72CC0F5FA2F0A66BEAB70ADA03C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3BFA1D0B01464EDCC1807DE0994B26D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Despite literature records noting 
<taxonomicName id="679604426AC55D1689F60B9C41125D2A" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="BA88E99624C02DB77428CD61DA365657" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Greece (
<bibRefCitation id="5441C61D334802139BC2981CAB115BF6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" author="Schulz, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B18" refString="Schulz, A, Heinze, J, Pusch, K, 2007. Description of two new Temnothorax species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Italy. Zootaxa 1471 (1): 1 - 14, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" title="Description of two new Temnothorax species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" volume="1471" year="2007">Schulz et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), we consider its presence in this country as doubtful. By courtesy of Petr Werner (Prague), we had an opportunity to study specimens collected from the site mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="C8F175A0E33AE76CE045E31E362634FC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" author="Schulz, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 14" refId="B18" refString="Schulz, A, Heinze, J, Pusch, K, 2007. Description of two new Temnothorax species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Italy. Zootaxa 1471 (1): 1 - 14, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" title="Description of two new Temnothorax species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1471.1.1" volume="1471" year="2007">Schulz et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
and compare them with a paratype of 
<taxonomicName id="3112E3AF583FBB04FEDE0D82ED1533F5" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="2D3F8CDD9AF22B866D4EB7CF1EAAA43C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and our Greek samples of members of the 
<taxonomicName id="17D6672CADFD543E8930EC3FE456D082" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Dlussky &amp; Zabelin" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax anodontoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="DDCCC493B878CCA8497606B55D2FB9EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Temnothorax anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. As a result, we concluded that the samples mentioned in the above-mentioned publication should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="89BA2CD1464821592C3C2723F91124DC" genus="T." lsidName="T. arkasi" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="arkasi">
<emphasis id="C2A7C68180E4708A41628D2093E61948" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. arkasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is also a record of 
<taxonomicName id="2E3DB1804418E35D3AC786A4DC8AB39A" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="1AE54B049B382202E9B197B0A9662C0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sheikhmosa in Iran (AntWeb.org, CFH000026). The photographs of this specimen certainly show a species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="52D8269FF0A521CAC11B75A80EEB8BCA" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Dlussky &amp; Zabelin" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax anodontoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="99BB9C801791C52365EE55D2BC02F5C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Temnothorax anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. However, its body coloration and presence of very small but distinct propodeal spines could indicate that it represents yet another undescribed species. In conclusion, the distribution of verified 
<taxonomicName id="02E9102401A960B2EA1B363307B086AA" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="7A31E63277244C10C55D0B2A67EA7C40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely restricted to Kopet Dag mountains in Turkmenistan.
</paragraph>
